title: Crews in Morocco pull earthquake survivor from building rubble
description: Rescue workers embraced each other after pulling a survivor from the rubble in the town of Moulay Brahim after a magnitude 6.8 earthquake struck Morocco.

title: G20 leaders' summit showcases India's growing global clout, as well as worries over press freedom
description: Much of New Delhi came to a halt this weekend as world leaders descended for the G20 summit with press denied access to almost all of it.

title: At age 36, Novak Djokovic wants his career of greatness to last a little longer
description: The Big Three is down to one and that last man standing is showing no signs of sitting down.

title: Vatican holds unprecedented beatification of Polish family of 9 killed for hiding Jews
description: In an unprecedented move, the Vatican on Sunday beatified a Polish family of nine — a married couple and their small children — who were executed by the Nazis during World War II for sheltering Jews.

title: North Korea’s Kim Jong Un has photo session, but quiet amid talk of Russia visit
description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un attended a photo session with participants celebrating the 75th anniversary of the country’s founding but stayed away from other events amid reports that he would soon leave for a trip to Russia.

title: Afghanistan is the fastest-growing maker of methamphetamine, U.N. says
description: Afghanistan is the world’s fastest-growing maker of methamphetamine, a report from the United Nations drug agency said Sunday.

title: Hundreds sleep outdoors in Marrakech after deadly earthquake in Morocco
description: Hundreds of people across Marrakech huddled together as they spent another night on the streets after Morocco's deadliest earthquake left many fearing their homes were no longer safe to return to.
